CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 21, 1959, pg. A22, reads: "'I Do, But I Don't' - As the marriage vows are exchanged and the ceremony ends, both the bride and groom relax. The mock wedding, which was held at the Kingsley House recently, is over.  Above are the members of the 'not-real' wedding party.  Left to right: Sandra Hobby, Audrey Wells, Robert Lamar, Kenneth Hines, Mildred McCloster, Marva Tibbs, Virginia Russell, Mary Ellen Orr, Charles Harris, Delbert Wells, Nathan Boykins and George.  Performing the ceremony is Vernon Russell, acting as minister, while the flower girl, Jacalyn Barbour, and the ring bearer, Edward Barbour, watch with curiosity. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of mock wedding participants, from left: Sandra Hobby, Audrey Wells, Robert Lamar, Kenneth Hines, Mildred McCloster, Marva Tibbs, Virginia Russell, Mary Ellen Orr, Charles Harris, Delbert Wells, Nathan Boykins, and George, with Vernon Russell performing ceremony, flower girl Jacalyn Barbour, and ring bearer Edward "Ed" Barbour, posed in Kingsley House
